				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Good spots for pulling large trains with 70-100+ mobs?<a name="52910"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 8:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hello.  Im looking for good spots to pull 60-100+ non caster mobs.  Must be blue to 65 since im AoEing em down for AA xp.  Thinking of trying Nadox.  But wondering if there are any other good spots?
<br />
The more HP they got the more mobs i need..
<br />
Forgot to say im a warrior, not a bard <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Editing in some extra info:  I got a cleric and enc botted at the same time. Im doing this as a single warrior, meaning high HP mobs require a lot of mobs.  Making PoP hard.  What im doing atm is the caller quest. One caller, 4 kegs.  Gives me 60 mobs, nicely packed on one spot.  Just invis., walk up and rampage. Then kill off the named after the spam/time stop.  Tried doing more than 1 caller, by pulling them together with my clerics and DB.  But it allways kills my cleric and its very hard to get them packed enough.  Best run was about 80 mobs killed.  Doing all 3 caller, spawning 180 mobs, makes it impossible due to the extreme lag with 180 mobs running after ye.  Still make half an AA pr 60 mobs, gotten some loot.. And i get to slack/read a book 90% of the time spent <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Hal</span></td>
