				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Good spots for pulling large trains with 70-100+ mobs?<a name="52933"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 11:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I believe only in HoH, but it may have affected other zones. Also, the nerf to Extended Notes and the changes from DX9 (mobs tend not to stack as easily as they used to, they interfere with each others' pathing) may make it difficult to maintain a kite of 50+ mobs.
<br />

<br />
That said, I am not familiar with many zones that have that many blue-to-65 mobs. Nadox, obviously. HoH as well but if most trash in in HoH has more than 10 or more NPCs on its hatelist (or some kind of list), they'll gate back to their spawn. You can see this with mage pet swarms; I believe this was the AE nerf to HoH. Droga may have that many mobs, but they're in the 63-67 range mostly. Nurga as well, though I think that's lightblue to 65. Grieg's End would have enough, but I don't know if the trash summons. Innovation, but the archaics and random spawning named summon. That's about all I can think of offhand. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
