			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Good spots for pulling large trains with 70-100+ mobs?<a name="53327"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 10:49 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Procs are based on a constant time basis and are completely delay independant.
<br />

<br />
For instance lets say your proc rate is 1 proc per minute (about average without WA I think). It doesn't matter what the delay of your weapon or what your haste is you will still average one proc per minute.
<br />

<br />
Now if you get slowed, obviously the proc rate per minute does not increase. However the chance of that first hit being a proc does increase.
<br />

<br />
For instance let's imagine you had a weapon that swung so slow it only went off once ever 30 seconds when you are slowed (take off haste items obviously). If your proc rate is once per minute you have a 50% chance of proccing on that first hit. Since rampage hits every mob within range at once, the slower you swing the higher the chance that your weapon will proc on that one swing. With 80 or so mobs that would be around 40 procs, each of which is an AE proc.
<br />

<br />
So with rampage groups the objective is to grab an AE'ng warrior weapon (earthshaker, no longer drops), get your delay as high as humanly possible (take off all haste items, get shaman slowed), gather the mobs all ontop of eachother if possible (some use furious) and then rampage when the disc wears off. Hopefully everything dies and you get a few AA's per pull.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td height="2"></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><a href="/Forums/AddPost.aspx?PostID=53327&amp;mode=flat"><img border=0 src=/skins/default/images/newpost.gif></a></td>
			</tr>
